.SH "NAME"
cz \- conventional commit message builder
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBcz\fP [\fB\-r\fP | \fB\-\-no\-require\-scope\fP] [\fB\-d\fP | \fB\-\-no\-defined\-scope\fP] [\fB\-e\fP | \fB\-\-no\-enforce\-patterns\fP] [\fB\-m\fP | \fB\-\-no\-multi\-scope\fP] [\fB\-q\fP] [\fB\-c\fP \fIFILE\fP] [\fISUBCOMMAND\fP]
.sp
\fBcz\fP \fBcreate\fP
.br
\fBcz\fP \fBlint\fP [\fB\-p\fP \fIPATHS\fP]
.br
\fBcz\fP \fBparse\fP
.br
\fBcz\fP \fBinit\fP [\fB\-o\fP \fIFILE\fP] [\fB\-f\fP]
.br
\fBcz\fP \fBhook\fP [\fBinstall\fP | \fBuninstall\fP | \fBstatus\fP]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBcz\fP is an interactive tool for creating commit messages that follow the
Conventional Commits specification. It can also lint existing messages or
display the resolved configuration.
.sp
When invoked without a subcommand, \fBcz\fP defaults to \fBcreate\fP mode if run
in a terminal, or \fBlint\fP mode if receiving input on standard input.
.SH "SUBCOMMANDS"
.sp
\fBcreate\fP
.RS 4
Compose a commit message interactively using \fBgum\fP(1). Prompts for type,
scope, breaking change indicator, description, body, and footer. Output
is written to standard output. Default when run interactively.
Requires \fBgum\fP to be installed.
.RE
.sp
\fBlint\fP [\fB\-p\fP \fIPATHS\fP]
.RS 4
Validate a commit message against the Conventional Commits rules and the
\fB.gitcommitizen\fP(5) configuration. Reads from standard input. Prints
diagnostic messages explaining any errors. Exits non\-zero if validation
fails. Use \fB\-e\fP to enforce scope matching against file patterns.
.sp
\fB\-p\fP, \fB\-\-paths\fP \fIPATHS\fP
.RS 4
Validate that the commit scope matches the specified file paths. Accepts a
space\-separated list of paths. Requires \fB\-e\fP (enforce\-patterns) to actually
validate the scope matches.
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBparse\fP
.RS 4
Display configuration with all values expanded. Useful for debugging.
.RE
.sp
\fBinit\fP [\fB\-o\fP \fIFILE\fP] [\fB\-f\fP]
.RS 4
Generate a starter \fB.gitcommitizen\fP configuration. Prints to standard output
by default, allowing piping or redirection.
.sp
\fB\-o\fP, \fB\-\-output\fP \fIFILE\fP
.RS 4
Write to \fIFILE\fP instead of stdout.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-f\fP, \fB\-\-force\fP
.RS 4
Overwrite an existing file (only with \fB\-o\fP).
.RE
.RE
.sp
\fBhook\fP \fBinstall\fP | \fBuninstall\fP | \fBstatus\fP
.RS 4
Manage the \fBcommit\-msg\fP git hook. \fBinstall\fP creates the hook to run
\fBcz lint\fP on each commit. \fBuninstall\fP removes it. \fBstatus\fP shows whether
the hook is installed.
.RE
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB\-c\fP, \fB\-\-config\-file\fP \fIFILE\fP
.RS 4
Use \fIFILE\fP instead of \fB.gitcommitizen\fP. Searches parent directories if
not specified.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-r\fP, \fB\-\-require\-scope\fP
.RS 4
Require a scope to be present. For \fBcreate\fP: removes the "(none)" option.
For \fBlint\fP: fails if commit has no scope. Overrides \f(CRrequire\-scope\fP config.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-no\-require\-scope\fP
.RS 4
Allow commits without scope. Overrides \f(CRrequire\-scope\fP config.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-d\fP, \fB\-\-defined\-scope\fP
.RS 4
Require scope to be defined in configuration. For \fBcreate\fP: removes the
"(custom)" option, only allowing configured scopes. For \fBlint\fP: fails if
scope is not in \f(CR[scopes]\fP. Overrides \f(CRdefined\-scope\fP config.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-no\-defined\-scope\fP
.RS 4
Allow any scope, even if not in configuration. Overrides \f(CRdefined\-scope\fP config.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-e\fP, \fB\-\-enforce\-patterns\fP
.RS 4
Enforce scope\-file pattern matching. Requires scope to match file patterns
from \f(CR[scopes]\fP when \fB\-\-paths\fP is provided. Also implies \fB\-d\fP (scope must
exist in config). Overrides \f(CRenforce\-patterns\fP config.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-no\-enforce\-patterns\fP
.RS 4
Disable pattern enforcement. Overrides \f(CRenforce\-patterns\fP config.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-m\fP, \fB\-\-multi\-scope\fP
.RS 4
Allow multiple scopes like \f(CRfeat(api,db):\fP. Overrides \f(CRmulti\-scope\fP config.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-no\-multi\-scope\fP
.RS 4
Disallow multiple scopes. Overrides \f(CRmulti\-scope\fP config.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP
.RS 4
Suppress warnings and non\-essential output.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
.RS 4
Display usage information and exit.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-V\fP, \fB\-\-version\fP
.RS 4
Display version information and exit.
.RE
.SH "FILES"
.sp
\fB.gitcommitizen\fP
.RS 4
Project configuration file. See \fBgitcommitizen\fP(5) for format. If no
configuration is found, the Angular convention is used (feat, fix, docs,
style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore, revert).
.RE
.SH "BEHAVIOR TABLE"
.sp
The \fB\-r\fP and \fB\-d\fP flags affect the \fBcreate\fP command:
.TS
allbox tab(:);
ltB ltB.
T{
.sp
Flags
T}:T{
.sp
create shows
T}
.T&
lt lt.
T{
.sp
default (no flags)
T}:T{
.sp
scopes + "(custom)" + "(none)"
T}
T{
.sp
\fB\-r\fP (require\-scope)
T}:T{
.sp
scopes + "(custom)" (scope mandatory, custom allowed)
T}
T{
.sp
\fB\-d\fP (defined\-scope)
T}:T{
.sp
scopes + "(none)" (can skip scope, no custom input)
T}
T{
.sp
\fB\-r \-d\fP (both)
T}:T{
.sp
scopes only (must pick configured scope)
T}
.TE
.sp
.sp
The \fB\-r\fP, \fB\-d\fP, and \fB\-e\fP flags affect the \fBlint\fP command:
.TS
allbox tab(:);
ltB ltB.
T{
.sp
Flag
T}:T{
.sp
lint behavior
T}
.T&
lt lt.
T{
.sp
default
T}:T{
.sp
Validates format only; scope is optional
T}
T{
.sp
\fB\-r\fP
T}:T{
.sp
Scope must be present
T}
T{
.sp
\fB\-d\fP
T}:T{
.sp
Scope must exist in config (if provided)
T}
T{
.sp
\fB\-e\fP
T}:T{
.sp
Scope must match file patterns (implies \fB\-d\fP)
T}
T{
.sp
\fB\-r \-e\fP
T}:T{
.sp
Scope required and must match patterns
T}
.TE
.sp
.sp
CLI flags always override config settings.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
Create and commit interactively
.RS 4
git commit \-m "$(cz)"
.RE
.sp
Create with required scopes (only configured scopes allowed)
.RS 4
git commit \-m "$(cz \-r \-d)"
.RE
.sp
Lint the last commit message
.RS 4
git log \-1 \-\-pretty=%B | cz lint
.RE
.sp
Lint before committing (commit\-msg hook)
.RS 4
cz lint < "$1"
.RE
.sp
Lint silently (exit status only)
.RS 4
cz lint \-q < "$1" || exit 1
.RE
.sp
Lint with scope validation against specific files
.RS 4
echo "feat(api): add endpoint" | cz lint \-\-paths "src/api/routes.ts"
.RE
.sp
Lint with scope\-file pattern enforcement
.RS 4
cz \-e lint \-\-paths "$(git diff \-\-cached \-\-name\-only)" < "$1"
.RE
.sp
Lint with multi\-scope enabled
.RS 4
echo "feat(api,db): cross\-cutting change" | cz \-m lint
.RE
.sp
Show resolved configuration
.RS 4
cz parse
.RE
.sp
Generate a starter configuration
.RS 4
cz init
.RE
.sp
Install the commit\-msg hook
.RS 4
cz hook install
.RE
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.sp
\fB0\fP
.RS 4
Success.
.RE
.sp
\fB1\fP
.RS 4
Runtime error (lint validation failed, missing dependency, config not found,
not a git repository).
.RE
.sp
\fB2\fP
.RS 4
Usage error (invalid arguments).
.RE
.sp
\fB130\fP
.RS 4
User cancelled (SIGINT).
.RE
